investigate the water state in Nafion and SPEEK. The RDF of S–S (S denotes sulfur atom in -SO3−) for Nafion and SPEEK is presented in Figure 5. As shown in Figure 5a, both RDFs of S–S (total) displayed a peak at about 4.5 Å. The peak intensity was largely ascribed to the intermolecular S–S correlation. Nafion exhibited much stronger peaks for all three types of S–S than SPEEK. In particular, the first S–S (intra) peak (4.5 Å) was missing in the RDF of SPEEK. This revealed that in SPEEK, the local aggregation of hydrophilic clusters, which was represented by sulfonate group, was poor, leading to poor cluster morphology, which agrees well with TEM results.
